# TAMS — UI Design System Rules

## Design Token Foundation

The single source of design truth is the CSS variable set generated by `shadcn@latest init`. Never override these variables inline or via Tailwind `[var(--...)]` hacks — update them in `src/index.css` if a value must change globally.

**Color palette:**
- All surfaces and text use the `slate` scale (neutral base). Never hardcode hex color values.
- The single accent color is `rose-700` (maps to `--primary` in the shadcn token set). Reserve it for primary CTA buttons, eligibility badges, active navigation indicators, and link underlines. Do not use it decoratively.
- Success states: `green-600 / dark:green-500`. Warning: `amber-600 / dark:amber-400`. Destructive: `red-600 / dark:red-500`. These match shadcn's semantic tokens.

**Typography:**
- Font family: `Inter` loaded via `@fontsource/inter`; system font stack as fallback. Set once in `src/index.css` via `font-family` on `:root`.
- Headings: `font-semibold`. Body and labels: `font-normal`. Never use `font-bold` on body text.
- Use only Tailwind's type scale (`text-sm`, `text-base`, `text-lg`, `text-xl`, `text-2xl`, `text-3xl`). No magic pixel values.

**Spacing:**
- Work on a 4 px grid. Every spacing value must be a Tailwind multiple of 1 (`p-1` = 4 px, `p-2` = 8 px, etc.).
- Minimum component padding: `p-4`. Minimum page content padding: `px-6 py-8` (desktop), `px-4 py-6` (mobile).

**Border radius:**
- Cards and panels: `rounded-lg`. Inputs, buttons, badges: `rounded-md`. Avatars and circular elements: `rounded-full`. These match shadcn defaults — do not fight them.

**Shadows:**
- Use `shadow-sm` on cards and inputs. `shadow-md` for popovers and dropdowns. `shadow-xl` only for modals and dialogs. Never use colored shadows or inset shadows for decorative purposes.

