## shadcn/ui Component Rules

- Add components individually via `npx shadcn@latest add <component>`. Never copy-paste component code manually; always use the CLI so versions stay consistent.
- All shadcn component source files live in `src/components/ui/`. Treat these as owned code — you may extend them, but keep changes minimal and purposeful.
- Extend shadcn components by composing them or passing `className` props with Tailwind utilities. Do not wrap a shadcn component in a styled `div` just to override its appearance.
- Form components must always be wired to `react-hook-form` + `zod`. The `shadcn Form` primitive handles error display — do not implement a parallel error-display mechanism.
- Use `shadcn Skeleton` for initial page loads. Use `shadcn Spinner` (or a `lucide-react Loader2` spinning icon) for user-triggered actions. Never show a blank area while data is loading.
- Use `shadcn Sonner` (toast) for transient success and error feedback. Do not use browser `alert()` or custom toast implementations.

---

## Dark / Light Mode

- `ThemeProvider` from `next-themes` must wrap the entire React tree in `src/main.tsx`. Configuration: `attribute="class"`, `defaultTheme="system"`, `enableSystem={true}`, `disableTransitionOnChange={false}`.
- The `ThemeToggle` component (`src/components/ThemeToggle.tsx`) is the only component allowed to call `useTheme()` from `next-themes`. Other components must not read or write the theme directly.
- All color choices must work in both modes without additional `dark:` overrides, because the shadcn CSS variable set switches automatically. Only add explicit `dark:` classes for cases the CSS variable system cannot cover (e.g. a custom gradient or a data-visualization color).
- Never use JavaScript to compute a color value for a style based on the current theme. If you think you need to, redesign using CSS variables instead.

