## Logo and Brand Usage

Brand assets live in `src/assets/logos/`. All brand assets must be accessed through wrapper components in `src/components/brand/` — never reference the raw image paths from feature or page components.

| Component | Asset | Where used | Constraints |
|---|---|---|---|
| `LogoFull` | `tams-logo-full.png` | `/login` page only | `max-w-[280px]`, centred |
| `LogoIcon` | `tams-logo-icon.png` | `AppShell` sidebar/header top-left | `h-8 w-auto` |
| `HacettepeLogo` | `hacettepe-logo.png` | `/login` page bottom-left corner | `max-w-[100px] opacity-60` |
| `HacettepeLogoHorizontal` | `hacettepe-logo-horizontal.png` | Reserved for `/about` or print views | — |

Rules:
- Logo components must accept an optional `className` prop forwarded to the `<img>` element; no other props.
- Always provide a descriptive `alt` attribute: `"TAMS — Transkript Analiz ve Mezuniyet Sistemi"` for `LogoFull`, `"TAMS"` for `LogoIcon`, `"Hacettepe Üniversitesi"` for Hacettepe variants.
- Do not apply colour filters, drop shadows, or opacity changes to logos outside the constraints listed above.

